                              <p class="Para">…need to know; to know the past, to know the traditional alternatives advocated by their ancestors, to know the specific experiences of their communities, and to know about the world that surrounds them (Deloria <span class="CitationRef"><a href="#CR13">1978</a></span>, p. 13).</p>
                                <p class="Para">Institute of Museum and Library Services’ Grants to Indian Tribes</p>
                                <p class="Para">Fourth Museum of the National Museum of the American Indian.</p>
                          <p class="Para">It places these initiatives within the broader Indigenous knowledge ecology.</p>
